Also, I don't think that a WlanThermoInputException is the correct thing to throw here if you get a TimeoutException. The WlanThermoInputException message implies incorrect data but a Timeout is not related to that at all, so the exception message would be misleading. Consider having the doGet method throw WlanThermoException instead so you can throw broader types of exceptions.

